msgctxt "dn1:0.2"
msgid "Brahmajālasutta "
msgstr "The Prime Net "

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "dn1:0.3"
msgid "1. Paribbājakakathā "
msgstr "1. Talk on Wanderers "

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-cs1.1, pts-vp-pli1.1, sc1
msgctxt "dn1:1.1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "dn1:1.1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā antarā ca rājagahaṃ antarā ca nāḷandaṃ addhānamaggappaṭipanno hoti mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was traveling along the road between Rājagaha and Nālanda together with a large Saṅgha of around five hundred mendicants. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.1.3"
msgid "Suppiyopi kho paribbājako antarā ca rājagahaṃ antarā ca nāḷandaṃ addhānamaggappaṭipanno hoti saddhiṃ antevāsinā brahmadattena māṇavena. "
msgstr "The wanderer Suppiya was also traveling along the same road, together with his pupil, the brahmin student Brahmadatta. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.1.4"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ suppiyo paribbājako anekapariyāyena buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṃghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati; "
msgstr "Meanwhile, Suppiya criticized the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha in many ways, "

msgctxt "dn1:1.1.5"
msgid "suppiyassa pana paribbājakassa antevāsī brahmadatto māṇavo anekapariyāyena buddhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṃghassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati. "
msgstr "but his pupil Brahmadatta praised them in many ways. "

#. VAR: anubandhā → anubaddhā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:1.1.6"
msgid "Itiha te ubho ācariyantevāsī aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā bhagavantaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhā honti bhikkhusaṃghañca. "
msgstr "And so both teacher and pupil followed behind the Buddha and the Saṅgha of mendicants directly contradicting each other. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.2, pts-vp-pli1.2, sc2
#. VAR: upagacchi → upagañchi (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:1.2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā ambalaṭṭhikāyaṃ rājāgārake ekarattivāsaṃ upagacchi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghena. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha took up residence for the night in the royal rest-house in Ambalaṭṭhikā together with the Saṅgha of mendicants. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.2.2"
msgid "Suppiyopi kho paribbājako ambalaṭṭhikāyaṃ rājāgārake ekarattivāsaṃ upagacchi antevāsinā brahmadattena māṇavena. "
msgstr "And Suppiya and Brahmadatta did likewise. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.2.3"
msgid "Tatrapi sudaṃ suppiyo paribbājako anekapariyāyena buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṃghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati; "
msgstr "There too, Suppiya criticized the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha in many ways, "

msgctxt "dn1:1.2.4"
msgid "suppiyassa pana paribbājakassa antevāsī brahmadatto māṇavo anekapariyāyena buddhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṃghassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati. "
msgstr "but his pupil Brahmadatta praised them in many ways. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.2.5"
msgid "Itiha te ubho ācariyantevāsī aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā viharanti. "
msgstr "And so both teacher and pupil kept on directly contradicting each other. "

# NOTE: saṅkhiyadhamma is a unique term, occurring, so far as I can tell, nowhere else in the Pali literature. The commentary glosses as kathadhamma, and thus Bodhi and Thanissaro effectively just have it as 'conversation". Rhys Davids followed by Wals have something like "trend of conversation." Yet it seems to me that such a unique term in such a prominent position should have a more specific maning. I am not aware of elsewhere in the ENTs where sankya has the plain sense "conversation". rather, it is connected with the notion of evaluation, measuring. Here the subject of discussion is the different ways the two parties evaluate the Sangha.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.3, sc3
msgctxt "dn1:1.3.1"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhitānaṃ maṇḍalamāḷe sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayaṃ saṅkhiyadhammo udapādi: "
msgstr "Then several mendicants rose at the crack of dawn and sat together in the pavilion, where the topic of evaluation came up: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn1:1.3.2"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso, yāvañcidaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sattānaṃ nānādhimuttikatā suppaṭividitā. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, reverends, it’s amazing how the diverse attitudes of sentient beings have been clearly comprehended by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.3.3"
msgid "Ayañhi suppiyo paribbājako anekapariyāyena buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati; "
msgstr "For this Suppiya criticizes the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha in many ways, "

msgctxt "dn1:1.3.4"
msgid "suppiyassa pana paribbājakassa antevāsī brahmadatto māṇavo anekapariyāyena buddhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati. "
msgstr "while his pupil Brahmadatta praises them in many ways. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.3.5"
msgid "Itihame ubho ācariyantevāsī aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā bhagavantaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhā honti bhikkhusaṅghañcā”ti. "
msgstr "And so both teacher and pupil followed behind the Buddha and the Saṅgha of mendicants directly contradicting each other.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.4, sc4
msgctxt "dn1:1.4.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ imaṃ saṅkhiyadhammaṃ viditvā yena maṇḍalamāḷo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "When the Buddha found out about this discussion on evaluation among the mendicants, he went to the pavilion, where he sat on the seat spread out and addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "dn1:1.4.2"
msgid "“kāya nuttha, bhikkhave, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā sannipatitā, kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti? "
msgstr "“Mendicants, what were you sitting talking about just now? What conversation was left unfinished?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn1:1.4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "The mendicants told him what had happened, adding, "

msgctxt "dn1:1.4.4"
msgid "“idha, bhante, amhākaṃ rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhitānaṃ maṇḍalamāḷe sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayaṃ saṅkhiyadhammo udapādi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:1.4.5"
msgid "‘acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso, yāvañcidaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sattānaṃ nānādhimuttikatā suppaṭividitā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:1.4.6"
msgid "Ayañhi suppiyo paribbājako anekapariyāyena buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:1.4.7"
msgid "suppiyassa pana paribbājakassa antevāsī brahmadatto māṇavo anekapariyāyena buddhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:1.4.8"
msgid "Itihame ubho ācariyantevāsī aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā bhagavantaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhā honti bhikkhusaṅghañcā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:1.4.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho no, bhante, antarākathā vippakatā, atha bhagavā anuppatto”ti. "
msgstr "“This was our conversation that was unfinished when the Buddha arrived.” "

# NOTE: I think this passage is more gently critical of the monks than implied in previous translations. The phrasing here is somewhat unusual and specific, and is more active than just “giving way”: they “should not do” what creates bitterness (i.e. sit around judging others). Cp MN 22, where the same phrases are used. In the Buddha’s case, it has the neutral hoti, while for the mendicants it uses karaniya, as here.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.5, pts-vp-pli1.3, sc5
msgctxt "dn1:1.5.1"
msgid "“Mamaṃ vā, bhikkhave, pare avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, dhammassa vā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, saṅghassa vā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, tatra tumhehi na āghāto na appaccayo na cetaso anabhiraddhi karaṇīyā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, if others criticize me, the teaching, or the Saṅgha, don’t make yourselves resentful, bitter, and exasperated. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.5.2"
msgid "Mamaṃ vā, bhikkhave, pare avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, dhammassa vā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, saṅghassa vā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, tatra ce tumhe assatha kupitā vā anattamanā vā, tumhaṃ yevassa tena antarāyo. "
msgstr "You’ll get angry and upset, which would be an obstacle for you alone. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.5.3"
msgid "Mamaṃ vā, bhikkhave, pare avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, dhammassa vā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, saṅghassa vā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, tatra ce tumhe assatha kupitā vā anattamanā vā, api nu tumhe paresaṃ subhāsitaṃ dubbhāsitaṃ ājāneyyāthā”ti? "
msgstr "If others were to criticize me, the teaching, or the Saṅgha, and you got angry and upset, would you be able to understand whether they spoke well or poorly?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn1:1.5.4"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.6, sc6
msgctxt "dn1:1.6.1"
msgid "“Mamaṃ vā, bhikkhave, pare avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, dhammassa vā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, saṅghassa vā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, tatra tumhehi abhūtaṃ abhūtato nibbeṭhetabbaṃ: "
msgstr "“If others criticize me, the teaching, or the Saṅgha, you should explain that what is untrue is in fact untrue: "

msgctxt "dn1:1.6.2"
msgid "‘itipetaṃ abhūtaṃ, itipetaṃ atacchaṃ, natthi cetaṃ amhesu, na ca panetaṃ amhesu saṃvijjatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is why that’s untrue, this is why that’s false. There’s no such thing in us, it’s not found among us.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
#. VAR: uppilāvitattaṃ → ubbilāvitattaṃ (bj, s1-3) | ubbillā­vitat­taṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:1.6.3"
msgid "Mamaṃ vā, bhikkhave, pare vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, dhammassa vā vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, saṃghassa vā vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, tatra tumhehi na ānando na somanassaṃ na cetaso uppilāvitattaṃ karaṇīyaṃ. "
msgstr "If others praise me, the teaching, or the Saṅgha, don’t make yourselves thrilled, elated, and excited. "

#. VAR: uppilāvitā → ubbilāvino (bj) | ubbilāvitattā (s1-3) | ubbillāvitā (pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:1.6.4"
msgid "Mamaṃ vā, bhikkhave, pare vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, dhammassa vā vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, saṃghassa vā vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, tatra ce tumhe assatha ānandino sumanā uppilāvitā tumhaṃ yevassa tena antarāyo. "
msgstr "You’ll get thrilled, elated, and excited, which would be an obstacle for you alone. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.6.5"
msgid "Mamaṃ vā, bhikkhave, pare vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, dhammassa vā vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, saṃghassa vā vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, tatra tumhehi bhūtaṃ bhūtato paṭijānitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "If others praise me, the teaching, or the Saṅgha, you should acknowledge that what is true is in fact true: "

msgctxt "dn1:1.6.6"
msgid "‘itipetaṃ bhūtaṃ, itipetaṃ tacchaṃ, atthi cetaṃ amhesu, saṃvijjati ca panetaṃ amhesū’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is why that’s true, this is why that’s correct. There is such a thing in us, it is found among us.’ "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn1:1.6.7"
msgid "2. Sīla "
msgstr "2. Ethics "

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "dn1:1.6.8"
msgid "2.1. Cūḷasīla "
msgstr "2.1. The Shorter Section on Ethics "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.7, sc8
msgctxt "dn1:1.7.1"
msgid "Appamattakaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhave, oramattakaṃ sīlamattakaṃ, yena puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "When an ordinary person speaks praise of the Realized One, they speak only of trivial, insignificant details of mere ethics. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.7.2"
msgid "Katamañca taṃ, bhikkhave, appamattakaṃ oramattakaṃ sīlamattakaṃ, yena puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya? "
msgstr "And what are the trivial, insignificant details of mere ethics that an ordinary person speaks of? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.8, pts-vp-pli1.4, sc9
msgctxt "dn1:1.8.1"
msgid "‘Pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo nihitadaṇḍo, nihitasattho, lajjī, dayāpanno, sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharatī’ti—"
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama has given up killing living creatures. He has renounced the rod and the sword. He’s scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion for all living beings.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.8.2"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "dn1:1.8.3"
msgid "‘Adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo dinnādāyī dinnapāṭikaṅkhī, athenena sucibhūtena attanā viharatī’ti—"
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama has given up stealing. He takes only what’s given, and expects only what’s given. He keeps himself clean by not thieving.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.8.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
#. VAR: ārācārī → anācārī (mr)
#. VAR: virato → paṭivirato (katthaci)
msgctxt "dn1:1.8.5"
msgid "‘Abrahmacariyaṃ pahāya brahmacārī samaṇo gotamo ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama has given up unchastity. He is celibate, set apart, avoiding the common practice of sex.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.8.6"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.9, sc12
#. VAR: theto → ṭheto (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn1:1.9.1"
msgid "‘Musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo saccavādī saccasandho theto paccayiko avisaṃvādako lokassā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama has given up lying. He speaks the truth and sticks to the truth. He’s honest and trustworthy, and doesn’t trick the world with his words.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.9.2"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "dn1:1.9.3"
msgid "‘Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo, ito sutvā na amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā na imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā, sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā samaggārāmo samaggarato samagganandī samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama has given up divisive speech. He doesn’t repeat in one place what he heard in another so as to divide people against each other. Instead, he reconciles those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting in harmony, loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.9.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "dn1:1.9.5"
msgid "‘Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo, yā sā vācā nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā bahujanamanāpā tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama has given up harsh speech. He speaks in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the heart, polite, likable and agreeable to the people.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.9.6"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.5, sc15
msgctxt "dn1:1.9.7"
msgid "‘Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya samphappalāpā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī, nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā kālena sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama has given up talking nonsense. His words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training. He says things at the right time which are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.9.8"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.10, sc16
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.1"
msgid "‘Bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama refrains from injuring plants and seeds.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.10.2"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave … pe …. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
#. VAR: virato → vikālabhojanā paṭivirato (pts1) | paṭivirato (katthaci)
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.3"
msgid "‘Ekabhattiko samaṇo gotamo rattūparato virato vikālabhojanā …. "
msgstr "‘He eats in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night and food at the wrong time.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.4"
msgid "Naccagītavāditavisūkadassanā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "‘He refrains from dancing, singing, music, and seeing shows.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.5"
msgid "Mālāgandhavilepanadhāraṇamaṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "‘He refrains from beautifying and adorning himself with garlands, perfumes, and makeup.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.6"
msgid "Uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "‘He refrains from high and luxurious beds.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.7"
msgid "Jātarūparajatapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "‘He refrains from receiving gold and money, "

#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.8"
msgid "Āmakadhaññapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "raw grains, "

#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.9"
msgid "Āmakamaṃsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "raw meat, "

#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.10"
msgid "Itthikumārikapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "women and girls, "

#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.11"
msgid "Dāsidāsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "male and female bondservants, "

#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.12"
msgid "Ajeḷakapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "goats and sheep, "

#. REF: sc27
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.13"
msgid "Kukkuṭasūkarapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "chickens and pigs, "

#. REF: sc28
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.14"
msgid "Hatthigavassavaḷavapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "elephants, cows, horses, and mares, "

#. REF: sc29
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.15"
msgid "Khettavatthupaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "and fields and land.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc30
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.16"
msgid "Dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "‘He refrains from running errands and messages; "

#. REF: sc31
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.17"
msgid "Kayavikkayā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "buying and selling; "

#. REF: sc32
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.18"
msgid "Tulākūṭakaṃsakūṭamānakūṭā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "falsifying weights, metals, or measures; "

#. REF: sc33
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.19"
msgid "Ukkoṭanavañcananikatisāciyogā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …. "
msgstr "bribery, fraud, cheating, and duplicity; "

#. REF: sc34
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.20"
msgid "Chedanavadhabandhanaviparāmosaālopasahasākārā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "mutilation, murder, abduction, banditry, plunder, and violence.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.10.21"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.22"
msgid "Cūḷasīlaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ. "
msgstr "The shorter section on ethics is finished. "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn1:1.10.23"
msgid "2.2. Majjhimasīla "
msgstr "2.2. The Middle Section on Ethics "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.11, sc35
#. VAR: seyyathidaṃ → seyyathīdaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:1.11.1"
msgid "‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te evarūpaṃ bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, "
msgstr "‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in faith, still engage in injuring plants and seeds. "

# NOTE: See my note on SN 22.54
#. VAR: pañcamaṃ → pañcamaṃ iti vā (bj, s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn1:1.11.2"
msgid "seyyathidaṃ—mūlabījaṃ khandhabījaṃ phaḷubījaṃ aggabījaṃ bījabījameva pañcamaṃ; "
msgstr "These include plants propagated from roots, stems, cuttings, or joints; and those from regular seeds as the fifth. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.11.3"
msgid "iti evarūpā bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama refrains from such injury to plants and seeds.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.11.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.12, pts-vp-pli1.6, sc36
msgctxt "dn1:1.12.1"
msgid "‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te evarūpaṃ sannidhikāraparibhogaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, "
msgstr "‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in faith, still engage in storing up goods for their own use. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.12.2"
msgid "seyyathidaṃ—annasannidhiṃ pānasannidhiṃ vatthasannidhiṃ yānasannidhiṃ sayanasannidhiṃ gandhasannidhiṃ āmisasannidhiṃ "
msgstr "This includes such things as food, drink, clothes, vehicles, bedding, fragrance, and material possessions. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.12.3"
msgid "iti vā iti evarūpā sannidhikāraparibhogā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama refrains from storing up such goods.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.12.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.13, sc37
msgctxt "dn1:1.13.1"
msgid "‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te evarūpaṃ visūkadassanaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, "
msgstr "‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in faith, still engage in seeing shows. "

# NOTE: uyyodhika in the suttas is only used here and at AN 10.30, where is not a sham. And the definition at Pc 50 says Uyyodhikaṃ nāma yattha sampahāro dissati “where strife is seen”.
#. VAR: meṇḍayuddhaṃ → meṇḍakayuddhaṃ (pts1)
#. VAR: sobhanakaṃ → sobhanagarakaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: mahiṃsayuddhaṃ → mahisayuddhaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: kumbhathūṇaṃ → kumbhathūnaṃ (bj, s1-3, mr)
#. VAR: dhovanaṃ → dhopanaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:1.13.2"
msgid "seyyathidaṃ—naccaṃ gītaṃ vāditaṃ pekkhaṃ akkhānaṃ pāṇissaraṃ vetāḷaṃ kumbhathūṇaṃ sobhanakaṃ caṇḍālaṃ vaṃsaṃ dhovanaṃ hatthiyuddhaṃ assayuddhaṃ mahiṃsayuddhaṃ usabhayuddhaṃ ajayuddhaṃ meṇḍayuddhaṃ kukkuṭayuddhaṃ vaṭṭakayuddhaṃ daṇḍayuddhaṃ muṭṭhiyuddhaṃ nibbuddhaṃ uyyodhikaṃ balaggaṃ senābyūhaṃ anīkadassanaṃ "
msgstr "This includes such things as dancing, singing, music, performances, and storytelling; clapping, gongs, and kettle-drums; art exhibitions and acrobatic displays; battles of elephants, horses, buffaloes, bulls, goats, rams, chickens, and quails; staff-fights, boxing, and wrestling; combat, roll calls of the armed forces, battle-formations, and regimental reviews. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.13.3"
msgid "iti vā iti evarūpā visūkadassanā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama refrains from such shows.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.13.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

# NOTE: While gambling isn’t mentioned explicitly here, jūtappamādaṭṭhānānuyoga is treated in DN 31 exclusively as gambling, so it seems that is implied.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.14, pts-vp-pli1.7, sc38
msgctxt "dn1:1.14.1"
msgid "‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te evarūpaṃ jūtappamādaṭṭhānānuyogaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, "
msgstr "‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in faith, still engage in gambling that causes negligence. "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/some-brief-notes-on-games/5329
#. VAR: ciṅgulikaṃ → ciṅgulakaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "dn1:1.14.2"
msgid "seyyathidaṃ—aṭṭhapadaṃ dasapadaṃ ākāsaṃ parihārapathaṃ santikaṃ khalikaṃ ghaṭikaṃ salākahatthaṃ akkhaṃ paṅgacīraṃ vaṅkakaṃ mokkhacikaṃ ciṅgulikaṃ pattāḷhakaṃ rathakaṃ dhanukaṃ akkharikaṃ manesikaṃ yathāvajjaṃ "
msgstr "This includes such things as checkers, draughts, checkers in the air, hopscotch, spillikins, board-games, tip-cat, drawing straws, dice, leaf-flutes, toy plows, somersaults, pinwheels, toy measures, toy carts, toy bows, guessing words from syllables, and guessing another’s thoughts. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.14.3"
msgid "iti vā iti evarūpā jūtappamādaṭṭhānānuyogā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama refrains from such gambling.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.14.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.15, sc39
msgctxt "dn1:1.15.1"
msgid "‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te evarūpaṃ uccāsayanamahāsayanaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, "
msgstr "‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in faith, still make use of high and luxurious bedding. "

#. VAR: hatthattharaṃ assattharaṃ rathattharaṃ → hatthat­thara­ṇaṃ assattharaṇaṃ rathattharaṇaṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn1:1.15.2"
msgid "seyyathidaṃ—āsandiṃ pallaṅkaṃ gonakaṃ cittakaṃ paṭikaṃ paṭalikaṃ tūlikaṃ vikatikaṃ uddalomiṃ ekantalomiṃ kaṭṭissaṃ koseyyaṃ kuttakaṃ hatthattharaṃ assattharaṃ rathattharaṃ ajinappaveṇiṃ kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇaṃ sauttaracchadaṃ ubhatolohitakūpadhānaṃ "
msgstr "This includes such things as sofas, couches, woolen covers—shag-piled, colorful, white, embroidered with flowers, quilted, embroidered with animals, double- or single-fringed—and silk covers studded with gems, as well as silken sheets, woven carpets, rugs for elephants, horses, or chariots, antelope hide rugs, and spreads of fine deer hide, with a canopy above and red cushions at both ends. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.15.3"
msgid "iti vā iti evarūpā uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama refrains from such bedding.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.15.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.16, sc40
msgctxt "dn1:1.16.1"
msgid "‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te evarūpaṃ maṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānānuyogaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in faith, still engage in beautifying and adorning themselves with garlands, fragrance, and makeup. "

#. VAR: daṇḍaṃ → daṇḍakaṃ (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: nāḷikaṃ → nālikaṃ (s1-3)
#. VAR: asiṃ → asiṃ khaggaṃ (s1-3, km) | khaggaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:1.16.2"
msgid "ucchādanaṃ parimaddanaṃ nhāpanaṃ sambāhanaṃ ādāsaṃ añjanaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ mukhacuṇṇaṃ mukhalepanaṃ hatthabandhaṃ sikhābandhaṃ daṇḍaṃ nāḷikaṃ asiṃ chattaṃ citrupāhanaṃ uṇhīsaṃ maṇiṃ vālabījaniṃ odātāni vatthāni dīghadasāni "
msgstr "This includes such things as applying beauty products by anointing, massaging, bathing, and rubbing; mirrors, ointments, garlands, fragrances, and makeup; face-powder, foundation, bracelets, headbands, fancy walking-sticks or containers, rapiers, parasols, fancy sandals, turbans, jewelry, chowries, and long-fringed white robes. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.16.3"
msgid "iti vā iti evarūpā maṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānānuyogā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama refrains from such beautification and adornment.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.16.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.17, pts-vp-pli1.8, sc41
msgctxt "dn1:1.17.1"
msgid "‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te evarūpaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, "
msgstr "‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in faith, still engage in unworthy talk. This includes such topics as "

#. VAR: itthikathaṃ → itthīkathaṃ (bj) | itthikathaṃ purisakathaṃ (s1, km, mr) | itthīkathaṃ purisakathaṃ (s2, s3)
msgctxt "dn1:1.17.2"
msgid "seyyathidaṃ—rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ mahāmattakathaṃ senākathaṃ bhayakathaṃ yuddhakathaṃ annakathaṃ pānakathaṃ vatthakathaṃ sayanakathaṃ mālākathaṃ gandhakathaṃ ñātikathaṃ yānakathaṃ gāmakathaṃ nigamakathaṃ nagarakathaṃ janapadakathaṃ itthikathaṃ sūrakathaṃ visikhākathaṃ kumbhaṭṭhānakathaṃ pubbapetakathaṃ nānattakathaṃ lokakkhāyikaṃ samuddakkhāyikaṃ itibhavābhavakathaṃ "
msgstr "talk about kings, bandits, and ministers; talk about armies, threats, and wars; talk about food, drink, clothes, and beds; talk about garlands and fragrances; talk about family, vehicles, villages, towns, cities, and countries; talk about women and heroes; street talk and well talk; talk about the departed; motley talk; tales of land and sea; and talk about being reborn in this or that state of existence. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.17.3"
msgid "iti vā iti evarūpāya tiracchānakathāya paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama refrains from such unworthy talk.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.17.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.18, sc42
msgctxt "dn1:1.18.1"
msgid "‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te evarūpaṃ viggāhikakathaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, "
msgstr "‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in faith, still engage in arguments. "

#. VAR: adhiciṇṇaṃ → āciṇṇaṃ (bj) | aviciṇṇaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:1.18.2"
msgid "seyyathidaṃ—na tvaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānāsi, ahaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānāmi, kiṃ tvaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānissasi, micchā paṭipanno tvamasi, ahamasmi sammā paṭipanno, sahitaṃ me, asahitaṃ te, purevacanīyaṃ pacchā avaca, pacchāvacanīyaṃ pure avaca, adhiciṇṇaṃ te viparāvattaṃ, āropito te vādo, niggahito tvamasi, cara vādappamokkhāya, nibbeṭhehi vā sace pahosīti "
msgstr "They say such things as: “You don’t understand this teaching and training. I understand this teaching and training. What, you understand this teaching and training? You’re practicing wrong. I’m practicing right. I stay on topic, you don’t. You said last what you should have said first. You said first what you should have said last. What you’ve thought so much about has been disproved. Your doctrine is refuted. Go on, save your doctrine! You’re trapped; get yourself out of this—if you can!” "

msgctxt "dn1:1.18.3"
msgid "iti vā iti evarūpāya viggāhikakathāya paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama refrains from such argumentative talk.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.18.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.19, sc43
msgctxt "dn1:1.19.1"
msgid "‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te evarūpaṃ dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, "
msgstr "‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in faith, still engage in running errands and messages. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.19.2"
msgid "seyyathidaṃ—raññaṃ, rājamahāmattānaṃ, khattiyānaṃ, brāhmaṇānaṃ, gahapatikānaṃ, kumārānaṃ “idha gaccha, amutrāgaccha, idaṃ hara, amutra idaṃ āharā”ti "
msgstr "This includes running errands for rulers, ministers, aristocrats, brahmins, householders, or princes who say: “Go here, go there. Take this, bring that from there.” "

msgctxt "dn1:1.19.3"
msgid "iti vā iti evarūpā dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama refrains from such errands.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.19.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.20, sc44
#. VAR: lābhena lābhaṃ nijigīsitāro ca → lābhena ca lābhaṃ nijigiṃsitāro (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:1.20.1"
msgid "‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te kuhakā ca honti, lapakā ca nemittikā ca nippesikā ca, lābhena lābhaṃ nijigīsitāro ca "
msgstr "‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in faith, still engage in deceit, flattery, hinting, and belittling, and using material possessions to pursue other material possessions. "

#. VAR: iti → iti (bj, mr)
msgctxt "dn1:1.20.2"
msgid "iti evarūpā kuhanalapanā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama refrains from such deceit and flattery.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.20.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn1:1.20.4"
msgid "Majjhimasīlaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ. "
msgstr "The middle section on ethics is finished. "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn1:1.20.5"
msgid "2.3. Mahāsīla "
msgstr "2.3. The Large Section on Ethics "

# NOTE: Translations of tiracchana in such contexts (debased, low, etc.) are often harsher than the old explanations. In Bhi pc 49-50, we have Tiracchā­na­vijjā nāma yaṃ kiñci bāhirakaṃ anat­tha­saṃhi­taṃ, while the commentary says Tiracchānavijjā nāma aniyyānikattā saggamokkhamaggānaṃ tiracchānabhūtā.
#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.21, pts-vp-pli1.9, sc45
msgctxt "dn1:1.21.1"
msgid "‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti, "
msgstr "‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong livelihood. "

#. VAR: khattavijjā → khettavijjā (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn1:1.21.2"
msgid "seyyathidaṃ—aṅgaṃ nimittaṃ uppātaṃ supinaṃ lakkhaṇaṃ mūsikacchinnaṃ aggihomaṃ dabbihomaṃ thusahomaṃ kaṇahomaṃ taṇḍulahomaṃ sappihomaṃ telahomaṃ mukhahomaṃ lohitahomaṃ aṅgavijjā vatthuvijjā khattavijjā sivavijjā bhūtavijjā bhūrivijjā ahivijjā visavijjā vicchikavijjā mūsikavijjā sakuṇavijjā vāyasavijjā pakkajjhānaṃ saraparittāṇaṃ migacakkaṃ "
msgstr "This includes such fields as limb-reading, omenology, divining celestial portents, interpreting dreams, divining bodily marks, divining holes in cloth gnawed by mice, fire offerings, ladle offerings, offerings of husks, rice powder, rice, ghee, or oil; offerings from the mouth, blood sacrifices, palmistry; geomancy for building sites, fields, and cemeteries; exorcisms, earth magic, snake charming, poisons; the crafts of the scorpion, the rat, the bird, and the crow; prophesying life span, chanting for protection, and animal cries. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.21.3"
msgid "iti vā iti evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama refrains from such unworthy branches of knowledge, such wrong livelihood.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.21.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.22, sc46
msgctxt "dn1:1.22.1"
msgid "‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti, "
msgstr "‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong livelihood. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.22.2"
msgid "seyyathidaṃ—maṇilakkhaṇaṃ vatthalakkhaṇaṃ daṇḍalakkhaṇaṃ satthalakkhaṇaṃ asilakkhaṇaṃ usulakkhaṇaṃ dhanulakkhaṇaṃ āvudhalakkhaṇaṃ itthilakkhaṇaṃ purisalakkhaṇaṃ kumāralakkhaṇaṃ kumārilakkhaṇaṃ dāsalakkhaṇaṃ dāsilakkhaṇaṃ hatthilakkhaṇaṃ assalakkhaṇaṃ mahiṃsalakkhaṇaṃ usabhalakkhaṇaṃ golakkhaṇaṃ ajalakkhaṇaṃ meṇḍalakkhaṇaṃ kukkuṭalakkhaṇaṃ vaṭṭakalakkhaṇaṃ godhālakkhaṇaṃ kaṇṇikālakkhaṇaṃ kacchapalakkhaṇaṃ migalakkhaṇaṃ "
msgstr "This includes reading the marks of gems, cloth, clubs, swords, spears, arrows, weapons, women, men, boys, girls, male and female bondservants, elephants, horses, buffaloes, bulls, cows, goats, rams, chickens, quails, monitor lizards, rabbits, tortoises, or deer. "

