msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.26, sc50
msgctxt "dn1:1.26.1"
msgid "‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti, "
msgstr "‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong livelihood. "

# NOTE: Omitting hanujappana as it is absent from comm.
msgctxt "dn1:1.26.2"
msgid "seyyathidaṃ—āvāhanaṃ vivāhanaṃ saṃvaraṇaṃ vivaraṇaṃ saṃkiraṇaṃ vikiraṇaṃ subhagakaraṇaṃ dubbhagakaraṇaṃ viruddhagabbhakaraṇaṃ jivhānibandhanaṃ hanusaṃhananaṃ hatthābhijappanaṃ hanujappanaṃ kaṇṇajappanaṃ ādāsapañhaṃ kumārikapañhaṃ devapañhaṃ ādiccupaṭṭhānaṃ mahatupaṭṭhānaṃ abbhujjalanaṃ sirivhāyanaṃ "
msgstr "This includes making arrangements for giving and taking in marriage; for engagement and divorce; and for scattering rice inwards or outwards at the wedding ceremony. It also includes casting spells for good or bad luck, curses to prevent conception, bind the tongue, or lock the jaws; charms for the hands and ears; questioning a mirror, a girl, or a god as an oracle; worshiping the sun, worshiping the Great One, breathing fire, and invoking Siri, the goddess of luck. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.26.3"
msgid "iti vā iti evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama refrains from such unworthy branches of knowledge, such wrong livelihood.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.26.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.27, pts-vp-pli1.12, sc51
msgctxt "dn1:1.27.1"
msgid "‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti, "
msgstr "‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong livelihood. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.27.2"
msgid "seyyathidaṃ—santikammaṃ paṇidhikammaṃ bhūtakammaṃ bhūrikammaṃ vassakammaṃ vossakammaṃ vatthukammaṃ vatthuparikammaṃ ācamanaṃ nhāpanaṃ juhanaṃ vamanaṃ virecanaṃ uddhaṃvirecanaṃ adhovirecanaṃ sīsavirecanaṃ kaṇṇatelaṃ nettatappanaṃ natthukammaṃ añjanaṃ paccañjanaṃ sālākiyaṃ sallakattiyaṃ dārakatikicchā mūlabhesajjānaṃ anuppadānaṃ osadhīnaṃ paṭimokkho "
msgstr "This includes rites for propitiation, for granting wishes, for ghosts, for the earth, for rain, for property settlement, and for preparing and consecrating house sites, and rites involving rinsing and bathing, and oblations. It also includes administering emetics, purgatives, expectorants, and phlegmagogues; administering ear-oils, eye restoratives, nasal medicine, ointments, and counter-ointments; surgery with needle and scalpel, treating children, prescribing root medicines, and binding on herbs. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.27.3"
msgid "iti vā iti evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama refrains from such unworthy branches of knowledge, such wrong livelihood.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.27.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc52
msgctxt "dn1:1.27.5"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, appamattakaṃ oramattakaṃ sīlamattakaṃ, yena puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "These are the trivial, insignificant details of mere ethics that an ordinary person speaks of when they speak praise of the Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn1:1.27.6"
msgid "Mahāsīlaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ. "
msgstr "The longer section on ethics is finished. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn1:1.27.7"
msgid "3. Diṭṭhi "
msgstr "3. Views "

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "dn1:1.27.8"
msgid "3.1. Pubbantakappika "
msgstr "3.1. Theories About the Past "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.28, sc53
msgctxt "dn1:1.28.1"
msgid "Atthi, bhikkhave, aññeva dhammā gambhīrā duddasā duranubodhā santā paṇītā atakkāvacarā nipuṇā paṇḍitavedanīyā, ye tathāgato sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti, yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "There are other principles—deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute—which the Realized One makes known after realizing them with his own insight. Those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak of these things. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.28.2"
msgid "Katame ca te, bhikkhave, dhammā gambhīrā duddasā duranubodhā santā paṇītā atakkāvacarā nipuṇā paṇḍitavedanīyā, ye tathāgato sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti, yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ? "
msgstr "And what are these principles? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.29, pts-vp-pli1.13, sc54
msgctxt "dn1:1.29.1"
msgid "Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbantakappikā pubbantānudiṭṭhino, pubbantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi. "
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who theorize about the past, and assert various hypotheses concerning the past on eighteen grounds. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.29.2"
msgid "Te ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha pubbantakappikā pubbantānudiṭṭhino pubbantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi? "
msgstr "And what are the eighteen grounds on which they rely? "

#. HTML: </p><h4>
msgctxt "dn1:1.29.3"
msgid "3.1.1. Sassatavāda "
msgstr "3.1.1. Eternalism "

#. HTML: </h4><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.30, sc55
msgctxt "dn1:1.30.1"
msgid "Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sassatavādā, sassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi. "
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who are eternalists, who assert that the self and the cosmos are eternal on four grounds. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.30.2"
msgid "Te ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi? "
msgstr "And what are the four grounds on which they rely? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.31, pts-vp-pli1.14, sc56
#. VAR: () → (parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe viga­tū­pak­kilese) (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn1:1.31.1"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā ātappamanvāya padhānamanvāya anuyogamanvāya appamādamanvāya sammāmanasikāramanvāya tathārūpaṃ cetosamādhiṃ phusati, yathāsamāhite citte () anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati. "
msgstr "It’s when some ascetic or brahmin—by dint of keen, resolute, committed, and diligent effort, and right focus—experiences an immersion of the heart of such a kind that they recollect their many kinds of past lives. "

#. VAR: udapādiṃ → upapādiṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:1.31.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi anekānipi jātisatāni anekānipi jātisahassāni anekānipi jātisatasahassāni: ‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṃgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ; tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṃgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti. Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati. "
msgstr "That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the cosmos contracting, many eons of the cosmos expanding, many eons of the cosmos contracting and expanding. They remember: ‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.’ And so they recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc57
msgctxt "dn1:1.31.3"
msgid "So evamāha: "
msgstr "They say: "

msgctxt "dn1:1.31.4"
msgid "‘sassato attā ca loko ca vañjho kūṭaṭṭho esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhito; "
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos are eternal, barren, steady as a mountain peak, standing firm like a pillar. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.31.5"
msgid "te ca sattā sandhāvanti saṃsaranti cavanti upapajjanti, atthi tveva sassatisamaṃ. "
msgstr "They remain the same for all eternity, while these sentient beings wander and transmigrate and pass away and rearise. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.31.6"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn1:1.31.7"
msgid "Ahañhi ātappamanvāya padhānamanvāya anuyogamanvāya appamādamanvāya sammāmanasikāramanvāya tathārūpaṃ cetosamādhiṃ phusāmi, yathāsamāhite citte anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi. "
msgstr "Because by dint of keen, resolute, committed, and diligent effort, and right focus I experience an immersion of the heart of such a kind that I recollect my many kinds of past lives, "

msgctxt "dn1:1.31.8"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi anekānipi jātisatāni anekānipi jātisahassāni anekānipi jātisatasahassāni: “amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ; tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno”ti. Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi. "
msgstr "with features and details. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc58
msgctxt "dn1:1.31.9"
msgid "Imināmahaṃ etaṃ jānāmi: "
msgstr "Because of this I know: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn1:1.31.10"
msgid "“yathā sassato attā ca loko ca vañjho kūṭaṭṭho esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhito; "
msgstr "“The self and the cosmos are eternal, barren, steady as a mountain peak, standing firm like a pillar. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.31.11"
msgid "te ca sattā sandhāvanti saṃsaranti cavanti upapajjanti, atthi tveva sassatisaman”’ti. "
msgstr "They remain the same for all eternity, while these sentient beings wander and transmigrate and pass away and rearise.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.31.12"
msgid "Idaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamaṃ ṭhānaṃ, yaṃ āgamma yaṃ ārabbha eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti. (1: 1) "
msgstr "This is the first ground on which some ascetics and brahmins rely to assert that the self and the cosmos are eternal. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.32, pts-vp-pli1.15, sc59
msgctxt "dn1:1.32.1"
msgid "Dutiye ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti? "
msgstr "And what is the second ground on which they rely? "

msgctxt "dn1:1.32.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā ātappamanvāya padhānamanvāya anuyogamanvāya appamādamanvāya sammāmanasikāramanvāya tathārūpaṃ cetosamādhiṃ phusati, yathāsamāhite citte anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati. "
msgstr "It’s when some ascetic or brahmin—by dint of keen, resolute, committed, and diligent effort, and right focus—experiences an immersion of the heart of such a kind that they recollect their many kinds of past lives. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.32.3"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—ekampi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭaṃ dvepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni tīṇipi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni cattāripi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni pañcapi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni dasapi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni: ‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ; tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti. Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati. "
msgstr "That is: one eon of the cosmos contracting and expanding; two, three, four, five, or ten eons of the cosmos contracting and expanding. They remember: ‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.’ And so they recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc60
msgctxt "dn1:1.32.4"
msgid "So evamāha: "
msgstr "They say: "

msgctxt "dn1:1.32.5"
msgid "‘sassato attā ca loko ca vañjho kūṭaṭṭho esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhito; "
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos are eternal, barren, steady as a mountain peak, standing firm like a pillar. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.32.6"
msgid "te ca sattā sandhāvanti saṃsaranti cavanti upapajjanti, atthi tveva sassatisamaṃ. "
msgstr "They remain the same for all eternity, while these sentient beings wander and transmigrate and pass away and rearise. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.32.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn1:1.32.8"
msgid "Ahañhi ātappamanvāya padhānamanvāya anuyogamanvāya appamādamanvāya sammāmanasikāramanvāya tathārūpaṃ cetosamādhiṃ phusāmi yathāsamāhite citte anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi. "
msgstr "Because by dint of keen, resolute, committed, and diligent effort, and right focus I experience an immersion of the heart of such a kind that I recollect my many kinds of past lives, "

msgctxt "dn1:1.32.9"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—ekampi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭaṃ dvepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni tīṇipi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni cattāripi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni pañcapi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni dasapi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni: “amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ; tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno”ti. Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi. "
msgstr "with features and details. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc61
msgctxt "dn1:1.32.10"
msgid "Imināmahaṃ etaṃ jānāmi: "
msgstr "Because of this I know: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn1:1.32.11"
msgid "“yathā sassato attā ca loko ca vañjho kūṭaṭṭho esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhito, te ca sattā sandhāvanti saṃsaranti cavanti upapajjanti, atthi tveva sassatisaman”’ti. "
msgstr "“The self and the cosmos are eternal, barren, steady as a mountain peak, standing firm like a pillar. They remain the same for all eternity, while these sentient beings wander and transmigrate and pass away and rearise.”’ "

msgctxt "dn1:1.32.12"
msgid "Idaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyaṃ ṭhānaṃ, yaṃ āgamma yaṃ ārabbha eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti. (2: 2) "
msgstr "This is the second ground on which some ascetics and brahmins rely to assert that the self and the cosmos are eternal. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.33, sc62
msgctxt "dn1:1.33.1"
msgid "Tatiye ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti? "
msgstr "And what is the third ground on which they rely? "

msgctxt "dn1:1.33.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā ātappamanvāya padhānamanvāya anuyogamanvāya appamādamanvāya sammāmanasikāramanvāya tathārūpaṃ cetosamādhiṃ phusati, yathāsamāhite citte anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati. "
msgstr "It’s when some ascetic or brahmin—by dint of keen, resolute, committed, and diligent effort, and right focus—experiences an immersion of the heart of such a kind that they recollect their many kinds of past lives. "

msgctxt "dn1:1.33.3"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—dasapi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni vīsampi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni tiṃsampi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni cattālīsampi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni: ‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ; tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti. Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati. "
msgstr "That is: ten eons of the cosmos contracting and expanding; twenty, thirty, or forty eons of the cosmos contracting and expanding. They remember: ‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.’ And so they recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
