#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc149
msgctxt "dn1:3.6.8"
msgid "‘Nevantavā nānantavā attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā nevasaññīnāsaññī’ti naṃ paññapenti. (8: 50) "
msgstr "neither finite nor infinite.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.7, sc150
msgctxt "dn1:3.7.1"
msgid "Imehi kho te, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhamāghātanikā nevasaññīnāsaññīvādā uddhamāghātanaṃ nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti aṭṭhahi vatthūhi. "
msgstr "These are the eight grounds on which those ascetics and brahmins assert that the self lives on after death in a neither percipient nor non-percipient form. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.7.2"
msgid "Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā uddhamāghātanikā nevasaññīnāsaññīvādā uddhamāghātanaṃ nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti, sabbe te imeheva aṭṭhahi vatthūhi … "
msgstr "Any ascetics and brahmins who assert that the self lives on after death in a neither percipient nor non-percipient form do so on one or other of these eight grounds. Outside of this there is none. "

