#. HTML: </p><h4>
msgctxt "dn1:3.17.5"
msgid "3.2.5. Diṭṭhadhammanibbānavāda "
msgstr "3.2.5. Extinguishment in the Present Life "

#. HTML: </h4><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.19, sc160
msgctxt "dn1:3.19.1"
msgid "Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā diṭṭhadhammanibbānavādā sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti pañcahi vatthūhi. "
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who speak of extinguishment in the present life. They assert the ultimate extinguishment of an existing being in the present life on five grounds. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.19.2"
msgid "Te ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha diṭṭhadhammanibbānavādā sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti pañcahi vatthūhi? "
msgstr "And what are the five grounds on which they rely? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.20, sc161
msgctxt "dn1:3.20.1"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā evaṃvādī hoti evaṃdiṭṭhi: "
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view: "

msgctxt "dn1:3.20.2"
msgid "‘yato kho, bho, ayaṃ attā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāreti, ettāvatā kho, bho, ayaṃ attā paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto hotī’ti. "
msgstr "‘When this self amuses itself, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation, that’s how this self attains ultimate extinguishment in the present life.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:3.20.3"
msgid "Ittheke sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti. (1: 58) "
msgstr "That is how some assert the extinguishment of an existing being in the present life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.21, pts-vp-pli1.37, sc162
msgctxt "dn1:3.21.1"
msgid "Tamañño evamāha: "
msgstr "But someone else says to them: "

msgctxt "dn1:3.21.2"
msgid "‘atthi kho, bho, eso attā, yaṃ tvaṃ vadesi, neso natthīti vadāmi; "
msgstr "‘*That* self of which you speak does exist, I don’t deny it. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.21.3"
msgid "no ca kho, bho, ayaṃ attā ettāvatā paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto hoti. "
msgstr "But that’s not how *this* self attains ultimate extinguishment in the present life. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.21.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn1:3.21.5"
msgid "Kāmā hi, bho, aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā, tesaṃ vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā. "
msgstr "Because sensual pleasures are impermanent, suffering, and perishable. Their decay and perishing give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.21.6"
msgid "Yato kho, bho, ayaṃ attā vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, ettāvatā kho, bho, ayaṃ attā paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto hotī’ti. "
msgstr "Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, this self enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. That’s how this self attains ultimate extinguishment in the present life.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:3.21.7"
msgid "Ittheke sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti. (2: 59) "
msgstr "That is how some assert the extinguishment of an existing being in the present life. "

