msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn1:3.23.5"
msgid "Yadeva tattha pītigataṃ cetaso uppilāvitattaṃ, etenetaṃ oḷārikaṃ akkhāyati. "
msgstr "Because the rapture and emotional excitement there are coarse. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.23.6"
msgid "Yato kho, bho, ayaṃ attā pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati, sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti “upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī”ti, tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, ettāvatā kho, bho, ayaṃ attā paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto hotī’ti. "
msgstr "But with the fading away of rapture, this self enters and remains in the third absorption, where it meditates with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, “Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss”. That’s how this self attains ultimate extinguishment in the present life.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:3.23.7"
msgid "Ittheke sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti. (4: 61) "
msgstr "That is how some assert the extinguishment of an existing being in the present life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.24, pts-vp-pli1.38, sc165
msgctxt "dn1:3.24.1"
msgid "Tamañño evamāha: "
msgstr "But someone else says to them: "

msgctxt "dn1:3.24.2"
msgid "‘atthi kho, bho, eso attā, yaṃ tvaṃ vadesi, neso natthīti vadāmi; "
msgstr "‘*That* self of which you speak does exist, I don’t deny it. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.24.3"
msgid "no ca kho, bho, ayaṃ attā ettāvatā paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto hoti. "
msgstr "But that’s not how *this* self attains ultimate extinguishment in the present life. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.24.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn1:3.24.5"
msgid "Yadeva tattha sukhamiti cetaso ābhogo, etenetaṃ oḷārikaṃ akkhāyati. "
msgstr "Because the bliss and enjoyment there are coarse. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.24.6"
msgid "Yato kho, bho, ayaṃ attā sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, ettāvatā kho, bho, ayaṃ attā paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto hotī’ti. "
msgstr "But giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, this self enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. That’s how this self attains ultimate extinguishment in the present life.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:3.24.7"
msgid "Ittheke sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti. (5: 62) "
msgstr "That is how some assert the extinguishment of an existing being in the present life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.25, sc166
msgctxt "dn1:3.25.1"
msgid "Imehi kho te, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇā diṭṭhadhammanibbānavādā sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti pañcahi vatthūhi. "
msgstr "These are the five grounds on which those ascetics and brahmins assert the ultimate extinguishment of an existing being in the present life. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.25.2"
msgid "Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā diṭṭhadhammanibbānavādā sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti, sabbe te imeheva pañcahi vatthūhi … "
msgstr "Any ascetics and brahmins who assert the ultimate extinguishment of an existing being in the present life do so on one or other of these five grounds. Outside of this there is none. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.25.3"
msgid "pe … "
msgstr "The Realized One understands this … "

msgctxt "dn1:3.25.4"
msgid "yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "And those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak of these things. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.27, pts-vp-pli1.39, sc167
msgctxt "dn1:3.27.1"
msgid "Imehi kho te, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇā aparantakappikā aparantānudiṭṭhino aparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti catucattārīsāya vatthūhi. "
msgstr "These are the forty-four grounds on which those ascetics and brahmins who theorize about the future assert various hypotheses concerning the future. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.27.2"
msgid "Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā aparantakappikā aparantānudiṭṭhino aparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti, sabbe te imeheva catucattārīsāya vatthūhi … "
msgstr "Any ascetics and brahmins who theorize about the future do so on one or other of these forty-four grounds. Outside of this there is none. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.27.3"
msgid "pe … "
msgstr "The Realized One understands this … "

msgctxt "dn1:3.27.4"
msgid "yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "And those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak of these things. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.29, sc168
msgctxt "dn1:3.29.1"
msgid "Imehi kho te, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbantakappikā ca aparantakappikā ca pubbantāparantakappikā ca pubbantāparantānudiṭṭhino pubbantāparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti dvāsaṭṭhiyā vatthūhi. "
msgstr "These are the sixty-two grounds on which those ascetics and brahmins who theorize about the past and the future assert various hypotheses concerning the past and the future. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc169
msgctxt "dn1:3.29.2"
msgid "Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā pubbantakappikā vā aparantakappikā vā pubbantāparantakappikā vā pubbantāparantānudiṭṭhino pubbantāparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti, sabbe te imeheva dvāsaṭṭhiyā vatthūhi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena; natthi ito bahiddhā. "
msgstr "Any ascetics and brahmins who theorize about the past or the future do so on one or other of these sixty-two grounds. Outside of this there is none. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.30, sc170
msgctxt "dn1:3.30.1"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato pajānāti: "
msgstr "The Realized One understands this: "

msgctxt "dn1:3.30.2"
msgid "‘ime diṭṭhiṭṭhānā evaṅgahitā evaṃparāmaṭṭhā evaṅgatikā bhavanti evaṃabhisamparāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘If you hold on to and attach to these grounds for views it leads to such and such a destiny in the next life.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:3.30.3"
msgid "Tañca tathāgato pajānāti, tato ca uttaritaraṃ pajānāti, tañca pajānanaṃ na parāmasati, aparāmasato cassa paccattaññeva nibbuti viditā. "
msgstr "He understands this, and what goes beyond this. Yet since he does not misapprehend that understanding, he has realized extinguishment within himself. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.30.4"
msgid "Vedanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā anupādāvimutto, bhikkhave, tathāgato. "
msgstr "Having truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape from feelings, the Realized One is freed through not grasping. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.31, sc171
msgctxt "dn1:3.31.1"
msgid "Ime kho te, bhikkhave, dhammā gambhīrā duddasā duranubodhā santā paṇītā atakkāvacarā nipuṇā paṇḍitavedanīyā, ye tathāgato sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti, yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "These are the principles—deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute—which the Realized One makes known after realizing them with his own insight. And those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak of these things. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn1:3.31.2"
msgid "4. Attālokapaññattivatthu "
msgstr "4. The Grounds For Assertions About the Self and the Cosmos "

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "dn1:3.31.3"
msgid "4.1. Paritassitavipphanditavāra "
msgstr "4.1. Anxiety and Evasiveness "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.32, pts-vp-pli1.40, sc172
msgctxt "dn1:3.32.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi, tadapi tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ ajānataṃ apassataṃ vedayitaṃ taṇhāgatānaṃ paritassitavipphanditameva. "
msgstr "Now, these things are only the feeling of those who do not know or see, the agitation and evasiveness of those under the sway of craving. Namely, when those ascetics and brahmins assert that the self and the cosmos are eternal on four grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.33, sc173
msgctxt "dn1:3.33.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā ekaccasassatikā ekaccaasassatikā ekaccaṃ sassataṃ ekaccaṃ asassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi, tadapi tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ ajānataṃ apassataṃ vedayitaṃ taṇhāgatānaṃ paritassitavipphanditameva. "
msgstr "partially eternal on four grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.34, sc174
msgctxt "dn1:3.34.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā antānantikā antānantaṃ lokassa paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi, tadapi tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ ajānataṃ apassataṃ vedayitaṃ taṇhāgatānaṃ paritassitavipphanditameva. "
msgstr "finite or infinite on four grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.35, sc175
msgctxt "dn1:3.35.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā amarāvikkhepikā tattha tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭhā samānā vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjanti amarāvikkhepaṃ catūhi vatthūhi, tadapi tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ ajānataṃ apassataṃ vedayitaṃ taṇhāgatānaṃ paritassitavipphanditameva. "
msgstr "or they resort to equivocation on four grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.36, sc176
msgctxt "dn1:3.36.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā adhiccasamuppannikā adhiccasamuppannaṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti dvīhi vatthūhi, tadapi tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ ajānataṃ apassataṃ vedayitaṃ taṇhāgatānaṃ paritassitavipphanditameva. "
msgstr "or they assert that the self and the cosmos arose by chance on two grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.37, sc177
msgctxt "dn1:3.37.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbantakappikā pubbantānudiṭṭhino pubbantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi, tadapi tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ ajānataṃ apassataṃ vedayitaṃ taṇhāgatānaṃ paritassitavipphanditameva. "
msgstr "they theorize about the past on these eighteen grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.38, sc178
msgctxt "dn1:3.38.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhamāghātanikā saññīvādā uddhamāghātanaṃ saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti soḷasahi vatthūhi, tadapi tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ ajānataṃ apassataṃ vedayitaṃ taṇhāgatānaṃ paritassitavipphanditameva. "
msgstr "or they assert that the self lives on after death in a percipient form on sixteen grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.39, pts-vp-pli1.41, sc179
msgctxt "dn1:3.39.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhamāghātanikā asaññīvādā uddhamāghātanaṃ asaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti aṭṭhahi vatthūhi, tadapi tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ ajānataṃ apassataṃ vedayitaṃ taṇhāgatānaṃ paritassitavipphanditameva. "
msgstr "or that the self lives on after death in a non-percipient form on eight grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.40, sc180
msgctxt "dn1:3.40.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhamāghātanikā nevasaññīnāsaññīvādā uddhamāghātanaṃ nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti aṭṭhahi vatthūhi, tadapi tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ ajānataṃ apassataṃ vedayitaṃ taṇhāgatānaṃ paritassitavipphanditameva. "
msgstr "or that the self lives on after death in a neither percipient nor non-percipient form on eight grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.41, sc181
msgctxt "dn1:3.41.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā ucchedavādā sato sattassa ucchedaṃ vināsaṃ vibhavaṃ paññapenti sattahi vatthūhi, tadapi tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ ajānataṃ apassataṃ vedayitaṃ taṇhāgatānaṃ paritassitavipphanditameva. "
msgstr "or they assert the annihilation of an existing being on seven grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.42, sc182
msgctxt "dn1:3.42.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā diṭṭhadhammanibbānavādā sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti pañcahi vatthūhi, tadapi tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ ajānataṃ apassataṃ vedayitaṃ taṇhāgatānaṃ paritassitavipphanditameva. "
msgstr "or they assert the ultimate extinguishment of an existing being in the present life on five grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.43, sc183
msgctxt "dn1:3.43.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā aparantakappikā aparantānudiṭṭhino aparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti catucattārīsāya vatthūhi, tadapi tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ ajānataṃ apassataṃ vedayitaṃ taṇhāgatānaṃ paritassitavipphanditameva. "
msgstr "they theorize about the future on these forty-four grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.44, sc184
msgctxt "dn1:3.44.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbantakappikā ca aparantakappikā ca pubbantāparantakappikā ca pubbantāparantānudiṭṭhino pubbantāparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti dvāsaṭṭhiyā vatthūhi, tadapi tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ ajānataṃ apassataṃ vedayitaṃ taṇhāgatānaṃ paritassitavipphanditameva. "
msgstr "When those ascetics and brahmins theorize about the past and the future on these sixty-two grounds, these things are only the feeling of those who do not know or see, the agitation and evasiveness of those under the sway of craving. "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn1:3.44.2"
msgid "4.2. Phassapaccayāvāra "
msgstr "4.2. Conditioned by Contact "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.45, pts-vp-pli1.42, sc185
msgctxt "dn1:3.45.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi, tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "Now, these things are conditioned by contact. Namely, when those ascetics and brahmins assert that the self and the cosmos are eternal on four grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.46, sc186
msgctxt "dn1:3.46.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā ekaccasassatikā ekaccaasassatikā ekaccaṃ sassataṃ ekaccaṃ asassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi, tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "partially eternal on four grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.47, sc187
msgctxt "dn1:3.47.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā antānantikā antānantaṃ lokassa paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi, tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "finite or infinite on four grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.48, sc188
msgctxt "dn1:3.48.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā amarāvikkhepikā tattha tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭhā samānā vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjanti amarāvikkhepaṃ catūhi vatthūhi, tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "or they resort to equivocation on four grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.49, sc189
msgctxt "dn1:3.49.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā adhiccasamuppannikā adhiccasamuppannaṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti dvīhi vatthūhi, tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "or they assert that the self and the cosmos arose by chance on two grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.50, sc190
msgctxt "dn1:3.50.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbantakappikā pubbantānudiṭṭhino pubbantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi, tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "they theorize about the past on these eighteen grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.51, sc191
msgctxt "dn1:3.51.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhamāghātanikā saññīvādā uddhamāghātanaṃ saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti soḷasahi vatthūhi, tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "or they assert that the self lives on after death in a percipient form on sixteen grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.52, sc192
msgctxt "dn1:3.52.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhamāghātanikā asaññīvādā uddhamāghātanaṃ asaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti aṭṭhahi vatthūhi, tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "or that the self lives on after death in a non-percipient form on eight grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.53, sc193
msgctxt "dn1:3.53.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhamāghātanikā nevasaññīnāsaññīvādā uddhamāghātanaṃ nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti aṭṭhahi vatthūhi, tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "or that the self lives on after death in a neither percipient nor non-percipient form on eight grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.54, sc194
msgctxt "dn1:3.54.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā ucchedavādā sato sattassa ucchedaṃ vināsaṃ vibhavaṃ paññapenti sattahi vatthūhi, tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "or they assert the annihilation of an existing being on seven grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.55, sc195
msgctxt "dn1:3.55.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā diṭṭhadhammanibbānavādā sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti pañcahi vatthūhi, tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "or they assert the ultimate extinguishment of an existing being in the present life on five grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.56, pts-vp-pli1.43, sc196
msgctxt "dn1:3.56.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā aparantakappikā aparantānudiṭṭhino aparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti catucattārīsāya vatthūhi, tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "they theorize about the future on these forty-four grounds … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.57, sc197
msgctxt "dn1:3.57.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbantakappikā ca aparantakappikā ca pubbantāparantakappikā ca pubbantāparantānudiṭṭhino pubbantāparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti dvāsaṭṭhiyā vatthūhi, tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "When those ascetics and brahmins theorize about the past and the future on these sixty-two grounds, that too is conditioned by contact. "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn1:3.57.2"
msgid "4.3. Netaṃṭhānaṃvijjativāra "
msgstr "4.3. Not Possible "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.58, sc198
msgctxt "dn1:3.58.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.59, sc199
msgctxt "dn1:3.59.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā ekaccasassatikā ekaccaasassatikā ekaccaṃ sassataṃ ekaccaṃ asassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.60, sc200
msgctxt "dn1:3.60.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā antānantikā antānantaṃ lokassa paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.61, sc201
msgctxt "dn1:3.61.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā amarāvikkhepikā tattha tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭhā samānā vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjanti amarāvikkhepaṃ catūhi vatthūhi, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.62, sc202
msgctxt "dn1:3.62.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā adhiccasamuppannikā adhiccasamuppannaṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti dvīhi vatthūhi, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.63, sc203
msgctxt "dn1:3.63.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbantakappikā pubbantānudiṭṭhino pubbantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.64, pts-vp-pli1.44, sc204
msgctxt "dn1:3.64.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhamāghātanikā saññīvādā uddhamāghātanaṃ saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti soḷasahi vatthūhi, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.65, sc205
msgctxt "dn1:3.65.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhamāghātanikā asaññīvādā, uddhamāghātanaṃ asaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti aṭṭhahi vatthūhi, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.66, sc206
msgctxt "dn1:3.66.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhamāghātanikā nevasaññīnāsaññīvādā uddhamāghātanaṃ nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti aṭṭhahi vatthūhi, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.67, sc207
msgctxt "dn1:3.67.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā ucchedavādā sato sattassa ucchedaṃ vināsaṃ vibhavaṃ paññapenti sattahi vatthūhi, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.68, sc208
msgctxt "dn1:3.68.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā diṭṭhadhammanibbānavādā sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti pañcahi vatthūhi, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.69, sc209
msgctxt "dn1:3.69.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā aparantakappikā aparantānudiṭṭhino aparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti catucattārīsāya vatthūhi, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.70, sc210
msgctxt "dn1:3.70.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbantakappikā ca aparantakappikā ca pubbantāparantakappikā ca pubbantāparantānudiṭṭhino pubbantāparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti dvāsaṭṭhiyā vatthūhi, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "Now, when those ascetics and brahmins theorize about the past and the future on these sixty-two grounds, it is not possible that they should experience these things without contact. "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn1:3.70.2"
msgid "4.4. Diṭṭhigatikādhiṭṭhānavaṭṭakathā "
msgstr "4.4. Dependent Origination "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.71, pts-vp-pli1.45, sc211
msgctxt "dn1:3.71.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi, yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā ekaccasassatikā ekaccaasassatikā … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:3.71.2"
msgid "yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā antānantikā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:3.71.3"
msgid "yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā amarāvikkhepikā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:3.71.4"
msgid "yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā adhiccasamuppannikā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:3.71.5"
msgid "yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbantakappikā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:3.71.6"
msgid "yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhamāghātanikā saññīvādā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:3.71.7"
msgid "yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhamāghātanikā asaññīvādā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:3.71.8"
msgid "yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhamāghātanikā nevasaññīnāsaññīvādā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:3.71.9"
msgid "yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā ucchedavādā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:3.71.10"
msgid "yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā diṭṭhadhammanibbānavādā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:3.71.11"
msgid "yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā aparantakappikā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:3.71.12"
msgid "yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbantakappikā ca aparantakappikā ca pubbantāparantakappikā ca pubbantāparantānudiṭṭhino pubbantāparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti dvāsaṭṭhiyā vatthūhi, sabbe te chahi phassāyatanehi phussa phussa paṭisaṃvedenti tesaṃ vedanāpaccayā taṇhā, taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ, upādānapaccayā bhavo, bhavapaccayā jāti, jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti. "
msgstr "Now, when those ascetics and brahmins theorize about the past and the future on these sixty-two grounds, all of them experience this by repeated contact through the six fields of contact. Their feeling is a condition for craving. Craving is a condition for grasping. Grasping is a condition for continued existence. Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn1:3.71.13"
msgid "5. Vivaṭṭakathādi "
msgstr "5. The End of the Round "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc212
msgctxt "dn1:3.71.14"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ayaṃ imehi sabbeheva uttaritaraṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "When a mendicant truly understands the six fields of contacts’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape, they understand what lies beyond all these things. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.72, sc213
msgctxt "dn1:3.72.1"
msgid "Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā pubbantakappikā vā aparantakappikā vā pubbantāparantakappikā vā pubbantāparantānudiṭṭhino pubbantāparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti, sabbe te imeheva dvāsaṭṭhiyā vatthūhi antojālīkatā, ettha sitāva ummujjamānā ummujjanti, ettha pariyāpannā antojālīkatāva ummujjamānā ummujjanti. "
msgstr "All of these ascetics and brahmins who theorize about the past or the future are trapped in the net of these sixty-two grounds, so that wherever they emerge they are caught and trapped in this very net. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.46, sc214
#. VAR: udakadahaṃ → udakarahadaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn1:3.72.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dakkho kevaṭṭo vā kevaṭṭantevāsī vā sukhumacchikena jālena parittaṃ udakadahaṃ otthareyya. Tassa evamassa: ‘ye kho keci imasmiṃ udakadahe oḷārikā pāṇā, sabbe te antojālīkatā. Ettha sitāva ummujjamānā ummujjanti; ettha pariyāpannā antojālīkatāva ummujjamānā ummujjantī’ti; "
msgstr "Suppose a deft fisherman or his apprentice were to cast a fine-meshed net over a small pond. They’d think: ‘Any sizable creatures in this pond will be trapped in the net. Wherever they emerge they are caught and trapped in this very net.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:3.72.3"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā pubbantakappikā vā aparantakappikā vā pubbantāparantakappikā vā pubbantāparantānudiṭṭhino pubbantāparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti, sabbe te imeheva dvāsaṭṭhiyā vatthūhi antojālīkatā ettha sitāva ummujjamānā ummujjanti, ettha pariyāpannā antojālīkatāva ummujjamānā ummujjanti. "
msgstr "In the same way, all of these ascetics and brahmins who theorize about the past or the future are trapped in the net of these sixty-two grounds, so that wherever they emerge they are caught and trapped in this very net. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.73, sc215
msgctxt "dn1:3.73.1"
msgid "Ucchinnabhavanettiko, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa kāyo tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "The Realized One’s body remains, but his attachment to rebirth has been cut off. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.73.2"
msgid "Yāvassa kāyo ṭhassati, tāva naṃ dakkhanti devamanussā. "
msgstr "As long as his body remains he will be seen by gods and humans. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.73.3"
msgid "Kāyassa bhedā uddhaṃ jīvitapariyādānā na naṃ dakkhanti devamanussā. "
msgstr "But when his body breaks up, after life has ended, gods and humans will see him no more. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc216
msgctxt "dn1:3.73.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ambapiṇḍiyā vaṇṭacchinnāya yāni kānici ambāni vaṇṭapaṭibandhāni, sabbāni tāni tadanvayāni bhavanti; "
msgstr "When the stalk of a bunch of mangoes is cut, all the mangoes attached to the stalk will follow along. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.73.5"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, ucchinnabhavanettiko tathāgatassa kāyo tiṭṭhati, "
msgstr "In the same way, the Realized One’s body remains, but his attachment to rebirth has been cut off. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.73.6"
msgid "yāvassa kāyo ṭhassati, tāva naṃ dakkhanti devamanussā, "
msgstr "As long as his body remains he will be seen by gods and humans. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.73.7"
msgid "kāyassa bhedā uddhaṃ jīvitapariyādānā na naṃ dakkhanti devamanussā”ti. "
msgstr "But when his body breaks up, after life has ended, gods and humans will see him no more.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.74, sc217
msgctxt "dn1:3.74.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn1:3.74.2"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante, ko nāmo ayaṃ, bhante, dhammapariyāyo”ti? "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing! What is the name of this exposition of the teaching?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn1:3.74.3"
msgid "“Tasmātiha tvaṃ, ānanda, imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ atthajālantipi naṃ dhārehi, dhammajālantipi naṃ dhārehi, brahmajālantipi naṃ dhārehi, diṭṭhijālantipi naṃ dhārehi, anuttaro saṅgāmavijayotipi naṃ dhārehī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well, then, Ānanda, you may remember this exposition of the teaching as ‘The Net of Meaning’, or else ‘The Net of the Teaching’, or else ‘The Prime Net’, or else ‘The Net of Views’, or else ‘The Supreme Victory in Battle’.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc218
msgctxt "dn1:3.74.4"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "dn1:3.74.5"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. VAR: dasasahassī → sahassī (pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:3.74.6"
msgid "Imasmiñca pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne dasasahassī lokadhātu akampitthāti. "
msgstr "And while this discourse was being spoken, the galaxy shook. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn1:3.74.7"
msgid "Brahmajālasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

